Although the program is available freely, I won't complain if you want to
send me any amount of money to thank me for my efforts.
@endnode
@node Development "Development and Testing"

Development and Testing
-----------------------

SamplerUtility was developed on an Amiga 3000T/25MHz with 2 Meg CHIP / 10
Meg FAST memory.

SamplerUtility has been tested under Kickstart version 37.175, Workbench
version 38.12.
@endnode
@node Install "Installing"

Installing
----------

The following files should be contained in the same directory:

SamplerUtility
SamplerUtility.info
@endnode
@node Start "Starting"

Starting
--------

From Workbench, double-click on the SamplerUtility icon.
@endnode
